research/history/results.tsv:171:r170_1774873899	1774873899	ok	discard	0.14044544100761414	96	lowrank_expert_topk	1				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0170/round0170_standard_1774873324_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef1_k96_20260330_202211	a5a334b02a451f54f9b329f9251db22185a357bb			建议以 r152 为 reference，只改 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_expert_topk`。这是一轮严格 matched-cost 的新 family 对照：利用 r152 已验证的轻 trunk 配方，把成本压回 `<0.25x` 主战场，直接回答 `lowrank + expert` 是否能在相近成本下打败当前 low-cost anchor。	相对 r152 只改一个 env 参数 `ARCHITECTURE`，满足 param_only 单变量规则。选择 r152 而不是 r165/r164，是因为 r152 提供了当前已知最合适的轻 low-rank trunk 配方：`TRUNK_RANK=16, K=96, ACTIVE_EXPERTS=2, NUM_EXPERTS=64`，切到 `lowrank_expert_topk` 后能自然落回 `<0.25x` 带内；而从 r165 直接切 architecture 会继承更重的 trunk/K 组合，信息价值反而更低。选择 `lowrank_expert_topk` 而不是 `shared_routed_factorized_expert_topk` 或 `shared_lowrank_routed_expert_topk`，是因为后两者在当前 target 上已经给出较强低成本负信号；而 `lowrank_expert_topk` 最近一次 matched 对照 r143 虽在约 0.29x 才拿到 FVU=0.1273，但说明这条 family 至少有真实质量潜力。本轮主要风险是去掉 residual cleanup 后质量会回升到被现有 anchors 支配；但若它在约 0.24x 下仍能接近或优于 0.137 级别，就会直接给出当前主战场最有价值的新结构证据。	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0170_standard_1774873324.log
research/history/results.tsv:172:r171_1774874886	1774874886	ok	discard	0.15570902824401855	96	lowrank_expert_topk	1				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0171/round0171_standard_1774874402_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef1_k96_20260330_204008	8de2d56fb0836f83496917e93330bcae6be8f355			以 r170 为 reference，仅将 `lowrank_expert_topk` 的 `LATENTS_PER_EXPERT` 从 `224` 降到 `160`，测试这条扩展兼容的轻 trunk+routed-expert 路线能否把 total_cost 从约 `0.24x` 压到约 `0.21x`，同时仍保持对当前 low-cost `shared_routed_expert_topk` anchors 的竞争力。	这轮严格遵守单变量原则：以有效已跑通的 r170 为 reference，只改 `LATENTS_PER_EXPERT`。选择这条轴而不是 `TRUNK_RANK`，是因为它带来的 total_cost 下压更明显，能更直接回答 `lowrank_expert_topk` 是否真能在更低成本段形成新前沿；主要风险是 expert width 压缩过头后质量退化，但这正是本轮需要澄清的核心问题。	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0171_standard_1774874402.log
research/history/results.tsv:174:r173_1774876695	1774876695	ok	discard	0.2532755434513092	96	factorized_topk	1				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0173/round0173_standard_1774876481_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef1_k96_20260330_211447	8593c4d869fb90be8351a8792976cc42bef6caed			以 r171 为 reference，仅切到 `factorized_topk`，在保持 `K=96` 与当前低成本训练配方不变的前提下，执行一个新的 matched-cost direct-compatible architecture probe，测试更轻 factorized scorer 是否能在约 `0.22x` 成本下挑战现有 low-cost anchors。	这轮严格只改一个 env 参数 `ARCHITECTURE`。选择 r171 作为 reference，是为了在当前最相关的低成本 recipe 上做最干净的 architecture swap，而不是重新回到更重或更旧的 recipe。主要风险是 `factorized_topk` 作为单库直接兼容结构，质量可能仍明显弱于当前 shared+routed anchors；但若不做这一步，就无法排除“更轻 scorer 而非更复杂 MoE-like 结构”是否才是当前 `<0.25x` 区域更值得继续的方向。	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0173_standard_1774876481.log
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0003.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A residual two-branch encoder may reduce FVU at K=128 by letting the second encoder pass target what the first branch misses, which is directly aligned with the reconstruction objective. Test residual_topk at the same K=128 anchor point as a quality-first architecture probe.","summary":"mixture_topk was slightly worse than the topk anchor under normal runtime, so the next move is to try a different expressive family rather than spending another round on that branch. residual_topk is the most directly FVU-oriented next architecture because it explicitly allocates encoder capacity to residual errors.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"residual_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps the comparison clean and opens a new family with a stronger direct link to reconstruction quality than mixture routing. It is still a first prototype pass, so a mediocre result should not automatically rule out all multi-branch encoders.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["mixture_topk at K=128/ef8/signum archived under normal runtime with proxy FVU 0.3058621361851692, so soft expert mixing is not an immediate win over the anchor.","Round 3 opens residual_topk as a new quality-first family because its second encoder pass is explicitly aimed at reducing remaining reconstruction error."],"next_hypotheses":["If residual_topk shows proxy improvement, follow with a stabilization pass on optimizer or expansion factor before promotion.","If residual_topk is also flat or worse, try factorized_topk next rather than returning to smaller-K search."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0005.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"factorized_topk likely failed because its hidden mixer is too narrow and lossy; widening that stage and adding a gate should preserve more information before latent selection and materially improve FVU. Re-test factorized_topk at K=128 after this single architectural stabilization edit.","summary":"The first factorized_topk prototype was much worse than the anchor, but its implementation used a plain hidden layer with width equal to d_in, which is a likely bottleneck rather than a decisive family verdict. This round keeps the same family and K while upgrading the encoder to a wider gated mixer.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a coherent follow-up on the only family that produced a strongly different signal, and it targets an obvious implementation bottleneck instead of abandoning the branch too early. The edit increases encoder compute, so even a quality gain still needs later cost scrutiny.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/factorized_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The original factorized_topk prototype likely suffered from an overly narrow d_in-sized hidden bottleneck rather than only a bad family prior.","Round 5 stabilizes factorized_topk by replacing the narrow ReLU mixer with a wider gated hidden stage before latent projection."],"next_hypotheses":["If the stabilized factorized_topk proxy improves substantially, consider promotion or a follow-up quality pass with optimizer tuning.","If the stabilized factorized_topk remains poor under normal runtime, deprioritize the current built-in families and move to a genuinely new encoder family rather than more local tuning."]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0136.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\uff1ax_hat = \u03a3_{i\u2208S_{e*(x)}(x)} \u03b1_i(x) b_{e*(x),i}\uff0c\u7b49\u4ef7\u5730\u4e5f\u53ef\u5199\u6210 x_hat = \u03a3_e \u03a3_{i\u2208S_e(x)} 1[e=e*(x)] \u03b1_{e,i}(x) b_{e,i}\u3002\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u5728\u7ebf\u94fe\u8def\u662f\u201c\u8f7b\u91cf router \u9009 1 \u4e2a\u9759\u6001 expert \u5b50\u5e93 -> \u8be5\u5b50\u5e93\u5185 local top-k -> \u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u67e5\u8868\u52a0\u6743\u548c\u201d\uff1b\u9759\u6001\u5e93\u4e0d\u968f\u6837\u672c\u52a8\u6001\u751f\u6210\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64 `expert_topk` \u5c5e\u4e8e\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002`batch_topk`\u3001`adaptive_budget_topk` \u8fd9\u7c7b batch/sample-coupled family \u5c5e\u4e8e\u4e0d\u517c\u5bb9\uff0c\u53ea\u4fdd\u7559\u5386\u53f2\u53c2\u8003\uff0c\u4e0d\u8fdb\u5165\u5f53\u524d frontier\u3002\u4e3b\u5047\u8bbe\uff1a\u76f8\u5bf9 r25 \u4ec5\u628a `NUM_EXPERTS` \u63d0\u5230 128\uff0c\u53ef\u5728\u4fdd\u6301 `K=128` \u4e0e `ACTIVE_EXPERTS=1` \u7684\u77ed\u6fc0\u6d3b\u8def\u5f84\u4e0b\uff0c\u628a routed-only \u603b\u9759\u6001\u5bb9\u91cf\u63a8\u5230\u4e0e\u5f53\u524d\u4f4e\u6210\u672c `shared_routed_expert_topk` \u6700\u4f18\u70b9\u8fd1\u4f3c matched-cost \u7684 0.41x \u533a\u95f4\uff0c\u76f4\u63a5\u56de\u7b54 shared \u5206\u652f\u662f\u5426\u771f\u6709\u5fc5\u8981\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0136.json:41:      "\u5982\u679c\u8be5\u70b9\u5728\u7ea6 0.41x \u4e0b\u63a5\u8fd1\u6216\u4f18\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d `shared_routed_expert_topk K=128` \u7684 FVU=0.1010\uff0c\u5219\u4e0b\u4e00\u8f6e\u53ef\u56f4\u7ed5\u8fd9\u4e2a routed-only recipe \u505a\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u538b\u7f29\uff0c\u4f8b\u5982\u4ee5\u65b0\u70b9\u4e3a reference \u53ea\u6539 `K` \u6216 `LATENTS_PER_EXPERT`\u3002",
