research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/results.tsv:49:r47_1774219387	1774219387	ok	discard	0.371366947889328	24	factorized_topk	12				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0047/round0047_standard_1774219177_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef12_k24_20260323_063943	ea9f6cc8fd2da883cdc1ab7c55ab11ede296a113			Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `factorized_topk` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows the severe-stagnation policy by continuing the search over qualitatively different built-in families instead of any further scalar sweep.	I avoided LR, aux, K, and EF adjustments because 12 no-improve rounds means minor tuning is exhausted. I also kept the comparison at K=24 for direct frontier relevance while testing a family that is structurally different from the recent low-rank residual, gating, routing, and codebook branches.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0047_standard_1774219177.log
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/results.tsv:63:r61_1774224459	1774224459	ok	discard	0.12982133030891418	24	lowrank_factorized_residual	12				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0061/round0061_standard_1774224249_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef12_k24_20260323_080416	d389a2508b845fbe8ecc190d4d1f78d390665016			Added a new prototype family, `lowrank_factorized_residual`, in `sparsify/` and registered it in config/factory dispatch. The architecture applies the existing low-rank trunk first, then replaces the direct residual-to-latent scoring path with a factorized bottleneck residual encoder before final top-k selection. Validation passed on the concrete dispatched architecture: exact smoke test succeeded for `architecture=lowrank_factorized_residual, K=24, EF=12`, and all parameters received gradients in a backward check, so this round stays on the architecture axis without repeating the last DDP blocker.	This satisfies the severe-stagnation policy by introducing a genuinely different residual mechanism rather than another scalar or K sweep. The experiment remains pinned to `K=24, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`, so attribution stays clean. Main risk: plain `factorized_topk` previously lost badly at K=24, so the gain depends on moving factorization to the post-trunk residual regime rather than replaying the same failure in a different wrapper.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0061_standard_1774224249.log
