research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0061.json:25:    "self_review": "This satisfies the severe-stagnation policy by introducing a genuinely different residual mechanism rather than another scalar or K sweep. The experiment remains pinned to `K=24, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`, so attribution stays clean. Main risk: plain `factorized_topk` previously lost badly at K=24, so the gain depends on moving factorization to the post-trunk residual regime rather than replaying the same failure in a different wrapper.",
