research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0239.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u53ea\u505a\u5355\u6837\u672c top-k \u9009\u62e9\u4e0e\u7cfb\u6570\u8ba1\u7b97\uff0c\u90e8\u7f72\u4fa7\u4ecd\u662f\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 reference_round=r238 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `K=48`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `ARCHITECTURE=topk`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=signum`\u3001`LR=0.003`\u3001`AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u5728\u7ea6 0.30x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u5904\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u628a\u521a\u5efa\u7acb\u7684\u5de6\u7aef\u70b9 `topk@K32` \u7684 FVU=0.3199 \u7ee7\u7eed\u660e\u663e\u538b\u4f4e\uff0c\u5e76\u8865\u51fa `0.28x -> 0.31x` \u4e4b\u95f4\u7f3a\u5931\u7684 Pareto \u8fc7\u6e21\u70b9\u3002\u9009\u62e9\u8fd9\u4e00\u6b65\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u7ee7\u7eed\u5f00\u65b0 family\uff0c\u662f\u56e0\u4e3a r238 \u5df2\u8bc1\u660e\u6700\u7b80\u5355\u5355\u5e93\u7ed3\u6784\u5728\u8d85\u4f4e K \u5de6\u7aef\u4f18\u4e8e `factorized_topk@0.30x`\uff0c\u5f53\u524d\u6700\u9ad8\u4fe1\u606f\u91cf\u95ee\u9898\u53d8\u6210 topk \u5de6\u4fa7\u524d\u6cbf\u7684\u771f\u5b9e\u659c\u7387\uff0c\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u518d\u6b21\u5207\u5230\u6700\u8fd1\u5df2\u7ed9\u51fa\u8d1f\u4fe1\u53f7\u7684 `codebook_topk`\u3001`factorized_topk` \u6216 recipe \u5fae\u8c03\u7ebf\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0239.json:35:      "r238 \u5df2\u786e\u8ba4 `topk@EF1,K32` \u5728\u7ea6 0.28x \u6210\u672c\u5904\u4f18\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d\u6700\u5de6\u7aef `factorized_topk@0.30x`\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u5de6\u4fa7\u8d85\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u524d\u6cbf\u5e94\u7531 plain topk \u800c\u4e0d\u662f factorized scorer \u4e3b\u5bfc\u3002",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:7:  "family_name": "factorized_topk",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:19:    "hypothesis": "After repeated failures from gating, staged residual, batch-budget, and codebook families, the next fundamentally different mechanism is a low-rank feature-mixing encoder without residual trunks: `factorized_topk` at `K=24, EF=12` may improve latent scoring efficiency enough to recover a better mid-K FVU tradeoff than the recent non-frontier architectures.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:20:    "summary": "Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `factorized_topk` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows the severe-stagnation policy by continuing the search over qualitatively different built-in families instead of any further scalar sweep.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:23:    "family_name": "factorized_topk",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:30:        "value": "factorized_topk"
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:57:      "`factorized_topk` tests whether a low-rank mixing stage before support selection helps mid-K quality without the heavier residual or discrete machinery used in recent failed branches."
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:60:      "If `factorized_topk` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test K=16 to see whether the factorized scoring helps more under tighter sparsity.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:61:      "If `factorized_topk` clearly loses at K=24, reject this branch and move to another fundamentally different family such as `group_topk` rather than any scalar sweep.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0047.json:62:      "If `factorized_topk` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."
